body:
I ran into this myself - the fix is unfortunately fairly complex, but here's a hook I wrote that helps a bit

```ts
/** Account for many factors when determining if we can load the next page.
 *
 * This specifically handles this state transition:
 * 1. User scrolls to the end of the page
 * 2. Sentinel comes into view
 * 3. Next page is fetched - all searches should be paused until this is done
 * 4. Next page arrives (but sentinel is still visible!)
 * 5. New data renders, pushing sentinel off-screen
 * 6. Search can now be run again at a later point
 */
function useRefineWhenAllowed(
  inView: boolean,
  hasMore: boolean,
  searching: boolean,
  refineNext: () => void
) {
  const [canSearch, setCanSearch] = useState(true);
  useEffect(() => {
    if (canSearch && inView && hasMore && !searching) {
      setCanSearch(false);
      refineNext();
    }
  }, [inView, refineNext, hasMore, searching, canSearch]);

  // These have to be coordinated
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!searching && !inView) {
      setCanSearch(true);
    }
  }, [inView, searching]);
}

```

To use: 
1. use something like `react-intersection-observer` to detect if your sentinel DOM node is visible, I use useInView here
2. futher connect your component with `connectStateResults`

this looks like:

```ts
import {
  connectInfiniteHits,
  connectStateResults,
  InfiniteHitsProvided,
  StateResultsProvided,
} from "react-instantsearch-core";
import { useInView } from "react-intersection-observer";

const InfinitePageOfResults: FC<StateResultsProvided & InfiniteHitsProvided> = ({
  hits, // from connectInfiniteHits
  hasMore, // from connectInfiniteHits
  refineNext, // from connectInfiniteHits
  searching,  // from connectStateResults
}) => {
  const { ref: sentinelRef, inView } = useInView();

  useRefineWhenAllowed(inView, hasMore, searching, refineNext);

  <div>
    <SearchResultsHere hits={hits} />
    {hasMore && <div ref={sentinelRef}>Loading more...</div>}
  </div>
};

export const InfinitePage = connectInfiniteHits(connectStateResults(InfinitePageOfResults));
```
